    "en": {
      "title": "The Pentagon signs an air defense agreement with Ukraine",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Pentagon has signed a $182 million contract with US arms manufacturer Raytheon to manufacture NASAMS (National Advanced Surface-to-Air Missile Systems) for the Ukrainian military.",
        "Work on the short- and medium-range air defense weapons will take place at Raytheon's facility in Tewksbury, Massachusetts, with an estimated completion date of August 23, 2024, the US Department of Defense said in a statement on Friday.",
        "Earlier this week, US President Joe Biden announced another military aid package for Ukraine amid the conflict with Russia. At $2.98 billion, it is the largest to date and includes six NASAMS systems."
      ],
